FT  28 MAY 93 / IDB created 2,000 places in new inward investment projects
last year
THE INDUSTRIAL Development Board, Northern Ireland's main jobs agency,
created almost 2,000 places in 10 new inward investment projects last year.
A further 2,800 jobs were created in IDB companies which received financial
assistance in previous years, but almost 3,800 jobs were lost in client
companies.
The board says the investment projects, which created 1,945 jobs, involved
investment of Pounds 168m with the IDB contributing Pounds 50m.
